    "7302518": {
        "Desc": "Talk to the mysterious Aranara",
        "Step": "Another Aranara appears and claims to be Arama. The place you are in \"is Vanarana, but not the real Vanarana.\" Communicating with Aranara is indeed difficult, but two things are clear — one, help Aranara, and you can go to the real Vanarana; two, help Aranara, and you can get treasure. At least Paimon understands the latter.",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Aralila",
                    "T": "Aranishat, you should admit defeat. Don't be like a stubborn twig that refuses to bend against strong gusts. You will break just like it."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Aranishat",
                    "T": "Aralila, let's have another match after the moon sinks and the sun rises again!"
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
    "7302507": {
        "Desc": "Help the Aranara",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Oh? This is Vanarana... So many Aranara..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "It seems like the same place, but..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Ooh, Paimon gets it! It feels completely different!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Since we've arrived in Vanarana, it's time to get a Bija and help Rana."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "We need a Bija."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Hmm, according to Arana, we must get a Bija from Vanarana to help Rana."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Bija? I've heard the stories about it."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Anyway, this is the real Vanarana, or to be more precise, it's \"Mahavanaranapna\"..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Wh—What a long name! And there are so many \"a's\"!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Yes, but we usually don't use its full name because it's too long. If explained in Nara language..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Ah, I know. It's \"the Aranara Forest of Dreams\"."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "\"Dreams\"... So you're saying..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "That the Vanarana we just saw exists in reality?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "And we're in a dream now?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Hmm, it's a story from very, very long ago. I wasn't even a seed then, I was still in a slumber in Sarva. But after Vanarana was destroyed once, we started living in this dream."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Huh, interesting past..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "It's very scary! I heard even the sky turned black. Trees swayed like grass on a field under strong winds, and they fell to the ground. And then very, very scary monsters were everywhere."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Luckily, they are all stories, not memories. Anyway, if you wish to leave Vanarana's dream, sing the Rhythm of the Great Dream in front of Silapna, and it's the same to return here."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Come with me. Araja will find a way to get you a Bija."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
