    "7307006": {
        "Desc": "Talk to Arama and Arasudraka",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "\"Come, come, dreams of the sprouts, memories of the leaves...\""
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "\"Look, shining pomegranates, glowing Sunsettias...\""
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "I see. Aranaga's song and Aramaha's song have the same source..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "What do you mean, the same source...?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "Songs are like rivers. They derive from the same origin, the \"Sourcesong.\" She is the home to all songs and the source of all great rivers."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "Then, it changes when it is sung for different memories and different stories, just like how a great river diverges into creeks."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "Just like all the creeks eventually flow into the sea, all the songs eventually converge into one, into the Sourcesong."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "#So Aranara song gatherers have to find all the songs. That way, we can find the Sourcesong. Thank you, Nara {NICKNAME} and Paimon, for finding Aramaha's song."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "What an impressive aspiration."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "#Thank you, Nara {NICKNAME}!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Hmm... Songs will keep growing in numbers and changing along the way, so how can all the songs be found?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "But songs will keep growing in numbers..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "And so will Aranara. So, if we keep doing our best, there will be no problem!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "Aramaha's song can attract Healthy Dendrograna. His Ashvattha's Concourse should be sealed in the same way."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arama",
                    "T": "#Nara {NICKNAME} found his song, which means we can get to Ashvattha's Concourse right away!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "#Yes! Good luck, Nara {NICKNAME}, Paimon, and Arama! I'm going to get ready for Festival Utsava!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Leave it to us! See you at Festival Utsava, Arasudraka!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Arasudraka",
                    "T": "Bye!"
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
